      • getMaximumByteSize

        public int getMaximumByteSize()
        Returns an estimation of the number of bytes of this message encoding. This estimation will always be greater than the actual encoded size so it is safe to use it to allocate the encoding byte buffer.
        Returns:
        the estimation.
